reviewText: Regina Case is the lead in this very good film about a woman who decides to stop trying to find conventional happiness in relationships. Great style and score throughout, it finds a way to be both convincing and dramatic as a love tale, involving multiple loves. Great cast, great directing, and great lead.

This is one of those movies that you sit and watch to the end to see what comes out of this boring, immoral production!!!
I just don't get the point! Is this supposed to be entertainment?
